//Strings IN JAVA

/* SYNTAX
String s = new String();
String s2,s1;
s2 = "Abcd";
s1 = "frnd";

character array conevertd to string
char[] a = "hello";
String str = String(a);

String -> character array
String.toCharArray(str);

String s1=new String(a); // deep copy (new obj)
String s2=s;  // shallow copy (both point to same obj)

Strings are immutable

functions:
1. length of string -> int l = s.length();

2. getting char from string -> char a = s.CharAt(index)

3. s.getChars(int start, int offset,char[] array, int startindex_dest_arr)
	start is starting index
	offset is how may chars we want // optional if not specifed then all chars
	char array where it will be stored
	startindex_dest_arr -> optional means starting index of array

char[] arr = new char[10]
s.getChars(0,3,arr) // store first 3
s.getChars(s.length-3, 3, arr, 3) // store last 3 chars in continuation with first 3

4. subString(int start, int end)
String s1 = s.subString(3,5);

5. get position of char s="hello"
int position = s.indexOf('l'); -> 2
int nextPosi = s.indexOf('l',3); -> 3// search started from 3rd posi

6. s.getBytes(int start, int offset,byte[] array, int startindex_dest_arr)
byte[] arr = new byte[10];
s.getBytes(0,3,arr);

7. trim() ->
str = "Abcd Efg Hij"
str.trim() -> "AbcdEfghij"
*/ 